This file is used by the application to control visible features and behaviors of the app. It
is not necessarily intended to be modified by the end-user.

Only keys with values that are different than the defaults need to be specified in this file. 
If all of the defaults meet the needs of your app, then this file is not needed at all.

Rename this file to cpl.defs and pace the modifed file in the followinf directory:
Windows: the same directory as the executable file for the application.
Mac OS X: in the application package, in the Contents/Resources directory.



key                       values    default     description
---                       ------    -------     -----------
showSimpleTab             0,1       0           if 1, show the simple "Firmware Loader" device tab

allowLoadAfterWarning     0,1       0           if 1, allows firmware to be overwritten when possible
                                                  version/date errors are detected in the simple tab

showAdvancedTab           0,1       0           if 1, shows the advanced "Firmware Utils" device tab, 
                                                  usually for developers only

showDPC                   0,1       0           if 1, shows the "DPC" global bus tab, which shows 
                                                  measured DPC statistics. Windows only.

showSystem                0,1       0           if 1, shows the "System" global bus tab, which gathers 
                                                  information about the operating system, and any ohci1394
                                                  controllers. It will warn if any required MS hotfixes are 
                                                  not installed, and will check for compatibility of the
                                                  ohci controllers with testing by TCAT if available.

defaultFrmwSector         string    "dice"      the name of the flash file sector which is overwritten
                                                  by the simple firmware loader. if the sector is not
                                                  already present, then a warning is shown to the
                                                  user.

frmwSector[xxxx]          string    ""          the xxxx value is always padded with zeros to 4 digits, 
                                                  and matches the product id of the device. this 
                                                  corresponds to kTCAT_DICE_DEVICE_x_ID as defined in 
                                                  tcat_dice_myproduct.h  if this value is not set, 
                                                  then the defaultFrmwSector string is used

hideRatesIfSingle         0,1       1           if 1, the global controls for setting and viewing the
                                                  current sample rate are hidden if there is only
                                                  one possible sample rate advertized by the device

hideSyncsIfSingle         0,1       1           if 1, the global controls for setting and viewing the
                                                  current sync source are hidden if there is only
                                                  one possible sync source advertized by the device

showMeasuredSampleRate    0, 1      1           if 1, the measured sample rate is shown in the device general tab

vendorInfo1               string    ""          string to be displayed on the info tab
vendorInfo2               string    ""          string to be displayed on the info tab, below vendorInfo1
vendorInfo3               string    ""          string to be displayed on the info tab, below vendorInfo2

F5RefreshesColours        0,1       0           if 1, the F5 key will reread this file and update GUI colours
UseGeneratedColourShades  0,1       0           determines if the colours are individually specified, or generated by th app
                                                  if 0, the separately specified values below will be used for GUI elements
                                                  if 1, the GUI will generate the colour scheme based on the three HSV values below
BaseColourHue             0-361     361         HSV Hue for generated colour schemes
                                                  0-360 for standard colour hue
                                                  greater than 360 uses greyscale
BaseColourValue           0-255     225         starting HSV colour Value (brightness) for generated colour schemes
BaseColourSaturation      0-255     10          starting HSV Saturation value for generated colur schemes

UseBlendedColours         0,1       1		if 1, colour scheme is generated by blending from BlendColour1 to BlendColour2
BlendColour1              hex value FFFF99	RGB value, format is RRGGBB
BlendColour2              hex value 000033      RGB value, format is RRGGBB


